Handle multiple rowids: find duplicates and pick a single row.

Source: R/fixme_find_duplicated_rowid.R
handle_multiple_rowid.Rd

Handle multiple rowids: find duplicates and pick a single row.

fixme_find_duplicated_rowid(.data)

fixme_pick_one_row_by_rowid(.data)

Arguments

.data

A dataframe as those created with allo_order().

Value

A dataframe with a single row by each value of rowid.

See also

Other functions to manipulate equations: add_equations, allo_find, allo_lookup, allo_order

Examples

library(dplyr)

best <- allodb::scbi_tree1 %>%
  add_species(allodb::scbi_species, "scbi") %>%
  allo_find() %>%
  allo_order()

allo_evaluate(best)
